Layout.title: Dammtorplatz/Alsterufer, Hamburg, Germany
Layout.infoText:
Traffic network of downtown Hamburg, Germany: In the south runs the Ring 1, at the Dammtorplatz in the north unite two main roads into the Alsterglacis. Both are crossed by the Dammtorstraße and the Alsterufer in north / south direction. In addition, the Metrobus line 5, with 50 000 passengers daily Europes busiest bus line, runs via Dammtorstraße/Dammtorplatz.
The traffic volume is estimated, signal times are fictional.
